Executive Profile
Christopher G. McCourt  CFO, SVP, Treasurer, CFO of Pilgrim Bank, SVP of Pilgrim Bank and Treasurer of Pilgrim Bank, Pilgrim Bancshares, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 2 different industries.56$368,974As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Christopher G. McCourt has been the Chief Financial Officer of Pilgrim Bank since August 2011. Mr. McCourt serves as the Chief Financial Officer of Pilgrim Bancshares, Inc. Mr. McCourt serves as Senior Vice President and Treasurer of Pilgrim Bank and Pilgrim Bancshares, Inc. Mr. McCourt has been with Pilgrim Bank since 2011. His responsibilities include the management and supervision of Pilgrim Bank's accounting and financial reporting and retail division and consumer ... lending. He oversees the preparation of financial statements and budgets, capital planning initiatives and the asset/liability and investment management function. Mr. McCourt joined Pilgrim Bank from Bank of America Corp., where he served as its Senior Vice President. He has over 30 years of experience in the financial services industry. He served in various financial positions at Bank of America from 2004 to 2011 and at Fleet Bank and its predecessors from 1982 to 2004. Mr. McCourt volunteers for the Friends of the Homeless of the South Shore and the Scituate Community Christmas organization. Mr. McCourt holds a Degree in Accounting and Marketing from Boston College and an MBA from Bentley University.Read Full Background




